== Buttery Mash ==

Boil a full #kettle{}. Chop the @potatoes{450%g} into small 2cm chunks (peel first if you prefer).

Pour the boiled water into a large #saucepan with @salt{1/2%tsp}.

Add the potatoes to the water and cook until you can easily slip a knife through, ~{15-18%minutes}.

== Spiced Tomato Beef Mince Ragu ==

While the potatoes cook, halve, peel and chop the @onion{1}(halved, peeled and chopped) into small pieces.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

Once hot, add the @British beef mince{240%g} and onion. Fry until browned, ~{5-6%minutes}. Use a #spoon to break up the mince as it cooks, then drain and discard any excess fat.

Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw mince. It's cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Meanwhile, peel and grate the @garlic{1%clove}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}).

Once the mince is browned, add the garlic and @Central American style spice mix{1}(add less if you'd prefer things milder). Stir-fry for ~{30%seconds}.

Stir in the @tomato passata{}, @chicken stock paste{10%g}, @sugar{1}(for the sauce) and @water{75%ml}(for the sauce).

Bring to the boil, then lower the heat and simmer, stirring occasionally, until thickened, ~{5-6%minutes}.

== Cheese and Finishing ==

Meanwhile, grate the @mature cheddar cheese{60%g}.

Once the potatoes are cooked, drain in a #colander{} and return to the #pot, off the heat.

Add the @butter{20%g} and a splash of @?milk{} and mash with a #potato masher{} until smooth.

Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then cover with a #lid{} to keep warm.

Once the tomato sauce has thickened, stir through the @peas{120%g}.

Cook until piping hot, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Taste and season with @salt{} and @pepper{} if needed, then remove from the heat.

When everything's ready, serve the spiced beef ragu alongside the buttery mash.

Finish by scattering the cheese all over. Enjoy!